You never know where the journey might take you…

In fact you probably don’t even have the capacity to imagine just how amazing it could be, or how much your life has the possibility to change.

Sound healing has changed my life in every possible way.

Not just in the physical sense of bringing me such a beautiful life filled with doing what I love, gratitude, abundance (not just $$ but so much more on top of that), and incredible opportunities…

But in the change it has made in my entire being. It has helped me heal so much anxiety, stress, insecurity and fear, and release my toxic patterns, codependency and the beliefs that we’re holding me back.

When I look back now, it’s wild to see the difference. I am a different person now than before I found sound healing. Yet, deep down, I know I’m the person I always was. 

Sound just helped me unbury her from all the “shoulds”, the conditioning and the fear and brought me back home to myself.

And now my mission is to help you do the same. ✨✨✨

Real, incredible, life-altering change is possible when we follow our hearts. 💖✨🙏🏼

I can’t wait to start sharing my next sound healing online training later today - I designed this course to help you learn everything you need to become a sound healer AND to experience transformation through sound for yourself.

There’s still (just enough) time to join me! Sign up through the link in my bio and find out how sound can change your life ✨✨✨

You literally will never know unless you just go for it and try. ✨

Let me tell you something. There will always be fear. At every new stage of the journey, you will have to face it. You will have to decide whether to stay safe or whether to go after your dreams with no way of knowing how it will turn out.

And after a while it gets to be simple, because it comes down to this:

What is more scary - going for it and finding out what happens? 

Or letting the fear hold you back, staying exactly where you’re at right now and letting your dreams be only that - dreams - forever?

My new favourite journaling question when I’m making a big decision, investing in myself and my future, or making a big move on my dreams is this:

How will I feel if I don’t do it?

And the answer is usually something like this:

Maybe I’ll feel safer for a moment. But then I’ll feel stuck, like I’m staying small instead of growing, and longing for something that I really want but am to afraid to go after.

And how will I feel if I do it?

Expanded, excited, like I am growing and forging my own path going after my dreams. 

….when it comes down to a choice between staying where you’re at and creating the life you dream about, suddenly that decision starts to feel very simple.

For me, it’s worth the fear every time. ✨

And suddenly, there’s this moment. The moment when you realise you’re coming back to yourself.

You might not have even realised that you’d been gone, until you suddenly feel yourself arrive back home to you again.

Maybe it’s been days, or weeks since you felt this. Maybe it’s been years.

It’s normally a moment that’s quiet, still, nothing’s really happening, but inside you know something is happening in this moment that means ✨everything✨.

You take a breath that’s a little deeper, and it’s like you can feel yourself sink a little bit deeper into your body.

“Ahhhh. Yes. There I am.”

It’s like greeting yourself as an old friend. One you haven’t seen in a while. The recognition, the feeling of comfort, the relief of simply being yourself.

Isn’t it funny how that happens? We don’t even realise we’ve been gone until we’re back.

We don’t realise that we haven’t been feeling so good until we feel better.

It’s in the moments of stillness, of quiet, of simply being, where we can truly meet ourselves again.

It happened to me yesterday. I haven’t been feeling myself lately, I’ve been walking myself through a lot of growth, a lot of emotions and been working non stop on a lot of exciting new projects….and somewhere along the way I lost touch with me.

You might feel it too, like you get so swept up in “doing” all the things, you forget the importance of just “being”.

I noticed the moment when I came back, and it felt so good to remember myself. 🙏🏼✨

This is why I love sound, because it has the power to help us return to ourselves over and over again, deeper and deeper every time. 

The more you keep coming back to that space within yourself, the more you have a solid foundation, a “knowing” of who you are at your core and you are able to live from that space in your daily life.

It’s ok that we get lost, we just have to remember to take the time in stillness and be-ing, to find our way back 💖

You can join me on Wednesday this week for an online full moon soundbath to bring you back home to yourself ✨🙏🏼 click the link in my bio to rsvp!

#soundbath #soundbathmeditation #soundbathworld #beingnotdoing #crystalbowls #comebacktome #comehometoyourself

This is your reminder that life gets to be as fun and easy as you let it be ✨

We tend to over-complicate things. To focus on a narrow view and stress over the small stuff. 

It’s easy to get caught up in the “shoulds” and the stories.

Somehow we forget that we get to design our lives. And that it can literally be anything you want.

Why not let it all be play? Why not see it as one big game of make believe, that you have the power to make real if you choose?

Because that’s what it is ✨✨

If you can let go trying to force or control things….it will just flow. And you can choose to flow with it and see what happens next on this beautiful ride. 💖

It gets to be that simple. It gets to be effortless. Whatever you choose, it gets to be that.

Isn’t that magical? ✨

Sometimes I forget how much has changed.

Sometimes I get so caught up in growth and doing the next thing that I forget how far I’ve come.

In those moments, I bring myself back into the present and really look at this beautiful life I’ve created…and honestly, I’m in awe of it. ✨

When I look back now at my life before sound healing it’s like looking at a different person.

Of course I want to continue expanding and can’t wait to keep creating and sharing my work with even more people….and at the same time I have to stop and be grateful for everything that’s already here.

I literally live in a tropical paradise next to the beach.

I get to do what I love every single day and share my gifts with the world.

I create my own schedule, I am free from all the “shoulds” I used to live by. 

In the past year I have overcome so many mindset blocks, unhealthy patterns and limiting beliefs that were holding me back, keeping me small and blocking me from real abundance.

I have invested in myself in ways I never thought possible this year and seen it come back to me multiplied.

The past version of Rosie who lived in London and worked a 9-5 would dream of this life. 

The Rosie of one year ago even wouldn’t believe that this was possible…it would scare the hell out of her 😅

So here I am, remembering to be grateful in every moment for everything that this work has brought to me. For everything that has shifted. For all that I have created.

It’s beautiful and I’ll never stop being grateful that this is how I get to live and what I get to share with the world 💖🙏🏼

Everything in the entire universe is vibrating at its own frequency. ✨

When we work with sound, we have the power to change our own frequency on a cellular level. Our nervous system shifts, and we can access our subconscious mind which gives us the ability to rewire our thought patterns and belief system. 

In essence, sound has the power to change our own frequency.

And the vibration of our frequency has the ability to influence the frequency of everything around us.

In other words, our inner frequency shifts our outer world to match the vibration we are giving out.

Our outer world is a reflection of our inner world. 

So when we work with sound, we can not only shift how we feel inside: physically, mentally, emotionally, spiritually….

…It also has the power to shift our entire lives.

When we start vibrating at a different frequency, we attract things into our lives that match that frequency.

That’s why this work can feel like magic ✨

When we do the work on the inside, we get to be amazed at how easily the changes happen on the outside. 💖

I say it all the time, but since working with sound healing my life is completely different than the one I had before. 

To me this is proof of the power of sound. I see it in myself, and I see it every day in the lives of my clients 💖

Imagine how much could change if you practiced regularly with sound?!

And if you’re inspired to start a regular practice, click my links to join my GLOW sound subscription library with access to all my recordings ✨

At the start of 2022, I was standing under a waterfall in Costa Rica when I decided my word of 2022 and my intention for the year would be “Overflow”

When someone asked me what it meant, I said it would be an overflow of everything into my life: abundance, love, opportunities, experiences, expansion…all the things.

And wow. What a year it has been.

So much has happened. So much has changed. I’ve welcomed so much into my life and made so many big moves.

I’m really not sure what I would have thought if you’d told me at the start of this year that by the end of it I would have…

Started a school of sound healing to train other healers.

Started running my own dream retreats.

Quadrupled my income from the year before…just by sharing my soul’s work.

Worked with hundreds of incredible clients.

Held Soundbaths for 1000+ people all across the world.

Trained dozens of sound healers to follow their own path with sound.

Found a loving healthy relationship and broken my toxic relationship patterns.

Moved into a beautiful 3 bedroom in a tropical paradise and opened my own healing studio.

Found genuine deep self love and grounding within myself.

Fully stepped into my gifts and owned my power.

Found the confidence and healing to really let go of things that are not in alignment with how I want to live.

It’s been a wild ride. And don’t get me wrong - there have been a lot of ups and downs which I’m going to share much more about!

But when I really look at it and realise how full this year has been, I am just beyond grateful.

Sometimes the overflow, abundance and sheer beauty of it all is overwhelming. 💖✨

I haven’t decided on my word for 2023 just yet…but if this year is anything to go by who knows what will happen next! 

Let me know in the comments what you’re calling in for 2023 🙏🏼✨

I moved to Sayulita Mexico 2 years ago this week, and when I look at what has changed from then to now, it feels unbelievable and at the same time makes me believe SO strongly in the power of our own dreams and our ability to literally create whatever we want in our lives. 

When I got here I had only just decided to fully step into sound healing and coaching as my calling.

I was afraid to charge for my work. I had no idea how to create a business in sound healing or what that would look like. The impostor syndrome voice inside my head that said to me “who are YOU to call yourself a healer? How can you ask people to pay you for this” was louuuuud. 

The first week I arrived here was one of the toughest I’ve had in a long time. I was in a toxic relationship that made me feel stuck, angry and alone. I had just lost a really close friendship (one of my first intense friendship breakups) that shook me to my core. I was super anxious and one of the first nights I was here I had a horrible panic attack, feeling lost and hopeless in a strange apartment in a town where I knew no one. My parents started calling me every day just to check I was still ok.

Throughout this whole journey, it’s been those moments where things have got dark that have fuelled me into the biggest transformations. The moments where I have suddenly said to the universe “No more. This is not how I’m showing up any longer”

I focused on the life I wanted and pretty soon, the magic of this place started and things started to shift. I realised this was a place where I could really live the dream I’d been imagining for months before.

I chose to step into my calling. I chose to step into myself and really show up for the first time as the person I wanted to be.

And from there, it was amazing to see how quickly things started to show up in my life. 

From that lost girl, crying on the floor of her apartment, I created the life of my dreams. ✨🙏🏼

A beautiful home, a thriving business, booked out with sessions, running retreats and a sound healing school. And I know next year is going to be even bigger! ✨

I used to care a lot about what I was doing on New Year’s Eve.

Years ago, it used to be about where was the best party going to be, and trying to plan the best night ever with my friends.

Then it became about making sure I was starting the new year in a way that I wanted to go on into the next.

One year when I was finally escaping my abusive relationship I booked a last minute trip to Barcelona on my own because I was so desperate to make New Years a new start.

It used to be a time for my inner perfectionist to come out. I would get all the fomo and then hate it when things inevitably didn’t turn out as planned or it was an anticlimax after all that…

Today I realised, I really don’t mind what I’m doing as the clock strikes midnight, or any other time of the evening. I don’t mind if I find a cool event to go to or not, or how many friends I see.

The thing I really care about is making sure I take some time to sit with myself, reflect on the year, celebrate what has passed and set some intentions for what is coming in.

That’s where my magic is this year, what about you? ✨

“You used to run a marketing company? That’s good money. Why would you stop doing that?”

I can’t help but laugh. “Because it’s not just about money.” I shrug.

“It didn’t feel right. I wanted to do something that felt like it mattered and was ME.”

He looks at me, confused.

“But there’s no way you make that kind of money doing this work, huh?”

I smile sweetly.

“Actually, I make a lot more. I work less hours and I do something that I love.”

…..”Oh.”

This is a conversation that happened this week. At first, I felt uncomfortable. But then I pretty quickly started feeling empowered.

It was a reminder of just how far I’ve come and how many societal “norms” and beliefs I have overcome with this life I’ve created.

Many people probably wonder the same about my life or find it hard to believe it can be true, and I get it. Even for me it sometimes feels unbelievable that this is what I get to do and how I get to live. 

I used to have moments mid-soundbath where I would think to myself “I can’t believe I’m getting paid to do this!”

This month I made 4x my old corporate monthly salary. In just the first 10 days of 2023. And I did it by playing crystal bowls and living at the beach. The Rosie of two years ago wouldn’t have believed you if you told her this was possible and that this would be her life now. 

I could never have imagined that this is what would happen just by having the courage to follow my path. 

The biggest fear clients come to me with that is stopping them from pursuing the life of their dreams, is that they don’t know how they’ll make money. They don’t believe they can do what they love AND make enough money doing it. 

This conversation reminded me this week how much that belief is jut a story. Maybe it’s one we all have engrained deep within us, but it can still be unlearned. And when you do, anything is possible. ✨

This weekend was a tough one.

I woke up a few days ago with intense pain in my neck and shoulder which hasn’t gone away.

I had a deeeeep healing session which brought up a lot of things that I’ve been processing through.

It’s been hard to function in my usual ways, and things have felt difficult, sticky, and exhausting.

I got caught up in a lot of my old patterns of negative thinking, stories of “not enough”, self criticism and perfectionist tendencies, getting frustrated when things haven’t worked out the way I wanted them to.

Yesterday it was all coming up and I felt like the whole day was going wrong and not turning out how I wanted.

And then I chose to surrender. I let myself slow down and just be with the day (and myself) as it all was.

And magic unfolded.

I ended up finding these beautiful places I’d never visited before, just a short ride from my doorstep.

I reconnected with gratitude for all the beauty that was around me.

I remembered how grateful I am for my life even in the moments when it feels like things aren’t going so well.

I allowed myself to slow down, to stop chasing the “more”, and appreciate the things that are already here. I realised that what I thought were small things I take for granted are actually greater and more significant than I had been seeing them as.

I saw the magic that is all around me if I just allow myself to shift my mindset and experience it as it is.

Sometimes you just need a reminder.
Sometimes you just need to slow down and meet yourself and your life exactly where it’s at.
Sometimes you need to remember all it took to be where you are now, and that you used to dream of what you have in this moment. 
Sometimes you need to shift back into gratitude and see that where you are is beautiful.

Sometimes all you need is a new perspective to remind you of all the magic that is already here ✨

Gratitude is everything. 💖

This happened today….and I’m grateful ✨

Because it’s shown me how much I’ve grown.

It’s shown me how much I’ve learnt to trust. 

Two years ago when I broke a bowl I almost gave up and messaged my mentor crying, saying “is this a sign from the universe telling me I shouldn’t be doing this work”. Lol….good job I didn’t listen to that thought 😅😂

When I lost some bowls again last summer, I had a full-on anxiety melt-down, all my money fears came up and I felt like I had lost everything I’d worked so hard to build.

Yesterday, this accident happened mid-soundbath with some clients. I don’t think they even noticed. Because all I did was take a deep breath, and sink into trust. 

The trust that my beautiful bowl can be fixed. And if it can’t, the trust that I will move through it with grace and belief that it’s how it’s meant to be. 

The trust that I have a support network who will be able to help me get it sorted with ease. 

The trust that I have built a solid foundation for my business with the masculine structure to hold me when things go wrong (aka insurance and financial stability to help me take care of what I need)

The trust that there is always a lesson in everything, that I am being guided into deeper purpose. 

And most of all the trust in myself, that I can and will continue to share my work with the world no matter what. That I can weather the storms that come. That even though things might sound a little different for a while, it’s all happening as it needs to. ✨✨✨

I always tell my sound healing students that this practice and these bowls are here to teach us so much more than we realise. That they are here to support our growth and our journey in so many ways. That learning to sound healing is also a journey into healing the layers of ourselves that come up during this practice.

I’m grateful, because my beautiful broken bowl showed me yesterday how much it has helped me to heal within myself 🙏🏼✨

This weekend I welcomed this beautiful flute into my sound family ✨

This sound has been calling to me for a long time, and I’ve been waiting for the right flute to appear.

This weekend I was walking through town in Sayulita (where there have literally never been flutes for sale anywhere before in the 2 years I’ve lived here) and I said to my partner “I feel like we need to go in this store”. We walked in and on the table in front there was a pile of 10 flutes, waiting for me.

Something inside me had just known it was time. And when I picked this one up and played it, from the first note I knew it was mine.

Someone asked me today “how have you learnt how to play it already” and I said, “honestly, I think my soul just knows how to do it.”

And that’s how it is. Sometimes your soul just knows.

It was the same the first time I heard the crystal bowls. Something inside me just KNEW I had to learn to play them. 

One of my 1:1 clients messaged me this morning to tell me that since our last session she’s been reconnecting with singing and dancing, things that she loved as a child but had forgotten about in her adult life…and that it felt like her soul was reminding her of who she really was and what she had always loved to do. 

Sometimes you can’t explain it, but something in you just KNOWS there is something calling to you. Something waiting for you. Something that is meant to be yours.

And when you let everything else get quiet and really listen, you can hear it.

This is what I love about sound healing. How when you’re connecting with sound you’re not just listening to beautiful instruments, you’re listening to something deeper…

The sound of your own soul. ✨

What is yours calling you towards?

I was speaking on a podcast recently about creating the life of your dreams and how I ended up here.

And a powerful realisation came out…

That you have to let go of your expectations or trying to figure out “how” it will work out…because chances are you can’t even imagine the life that is waiting for you.

You can only imagine what you already believe to be possible. So if you try to imagine what it might look like, you might actually be limiting yourself.

I mean, seriously. If someone had asked me to imagine what my dream life could look like when I was living in London, stuck in a toxic relationship, working in a job that felt soulless and kept me stuck in a cycle of stress, burnout, boredom and drinking too much at the weekends because I felt like there wasn’t anything better to do….I couldn’t have even imagined that this is how I could be living now.

It felt so hard to get out of the life I had then because I couldn’t imagine anything else. I could only see what everyone around me was doing and it seemed like that was all there was. 

I felt like maybe there was something wrong with me because it seemed like I was the only one who felt in her soul like there must be more to life than this.

This is why it can be so scary to take the leap of faith into whatever your soul is calling you to do.

Even when you KNOW deep down that it’s something that could change your life and feels like exactly what you need, on a soul level.

Because you have no idea what that might look like. Because you don’t know yet that it’s possible.

But that’s where the magic is. Because when you can surrender to the not-knowing, take the first step you CAN take to move towards what is calling to you, you open yourself up for so much more than you could even believe.

You can’t think your way into it. There comes a point when you have to just leap. 

Leap and trust that your soul is guiding you to where you need to go, and one day soon you’ll look back and realise it’s even better than you could ever have imagined. ✨✨

I never intended to become a teacher. At the start of the training I said I was just doing it for me. For my own healing, to deepen my own practice and take my own journey.

I started that training totally lost, scared, insecure, unhealthy, out of touch with myself and stuck in so many bad habits, old patterns and painful emotions. 

In the closing circle, I remember crying as I realised that I had finally started to love myself again (or maybe truly for the first time ever).

That training was also the first time I heard the crystal bowls. And it was the first time I heard the call of my soul like a voice that switched on in the back of my head, telling me:

“You have to learn how to play the crystal bowls.”

I had followed the pull of my soul’s path to Bali, to my yoga teacher training, and now it was leading me here.

I had no idea why. But I decided to trust it and follow the path my soul was pulling me towards.

I never could have imagined where it would lead. But, here we are.

Magic happens when you learn to listen to that voice inside you, the call of your soul that deep down already knows what you’re being drawn to, when you find the courage to trust it and follow it.

Keep going. Trust the call of your soul. It’s guiding you home. ✨

And a lot of the time, the message it’s giving you is to surrender to trust.

The trust that everything is always working out for you no matter how it looks.

The trust that you have always got your own back. That you are always being held. 

The trust that the universe is always guiding you to what’s best for you, even if you don’t think it’s what you want at the time (I mean, if you look back, hasn’t it always been doing that, really?)

And when you can surrender to that trust and overcome the fear that keeps you trying to force things…? 

Life gets to be so fun and easy.

When you flow with where the universe is guiding you instead of resisting it, that’s when the magic happens.

How can you surrender and let it in? ✨✨✨

A little bit about me… ✨

Before I was a sound healer, I was…

💔 Training to be a singer, until I found out I had a hole in my vocal cords. I lost music from my life for 10 years before sound healing guided me back home to myself.

💔 A CEO running my own social media company. I was totally burnt out by working 9-5 in the city and felt totally unaligned with my soul

💔 Stuck in toxic and abusive relationships that left me with no self worth and questioning who I was.

💔 Struggling with anxiety and social anxiety that gave me regular panic attacks.

💔 Drinking too much. I relied on alcohol as a way to feel accepted, numb my feelings and lack of self and feel more comfortable in social situations.

💔 Lost and purposeless. I used to ask myself all the time “what am I really meant to be doing with my life?!” I felt unfulfilled and knew there was something more that was meant for me.

Since finding sound healing, I have:

✨ Healed my voice, found my true voice and share it with the world as part of my work. 

✨ Used my marketing skills to grow my business & teach others how to create their own healing businesses.

✨ Escaping my toxic relationship led me to Bali to heal, find myself again and become a yoga teacher. It was there that I first heard the crystal bowls and my whole path unfolded.

✨Sound Healing healed my anxiety and helped me find more peace within myself than ever before.

✨ The more I found alignment & stepped into meaningful healing work, I healed my relationship with alcohol and brought myself back to health.

✨ Sound Healing connected me with my purpose in a way beyond anything I could have imagined. I found my calling and myself. 

Looking at my life before and after becoming a sound healer is like looking at two completely different people’s lives. Sound Healing has the power to change everything.

Today I finally cancelled my UK phone number. I haven’t lived there for almost 5 years. 

But some part of me was still holding on to the last remnants of that life, the past version of me.

Isn’t it funny how we still sometimes hold on to the things we know it’s time to let go of?

I can’t tell you why it took me so long to change it. I’ve always been pretty good at letting go and changing. And I’ve made some very big changes in my life in the past 5 years.

I’ve let go of relationships, apartments, places in the world, friendships, old beliefs, anxiety, crystal bowls (😢), business partnerships, self doubt, my old marketing business…my entire old identity!

And why? Because we have to clear out the old to make space for the new. You have to energetically show the universe that you’re ready for change by letting go of what you no longer want.

Every time I’ve leaped and levelled up, I’ve had to go through a big clearing first. 

It’s something I’ve subconsciously been doing for my entire life. Every time I know it’s time for an energy shift, I clear out space. I clean out my closet, I throw things out, I clean the house, I move furniture around, I redecorate, I change my look. 

So if you’re feeling stuck, ask yourself what have you been holding on to?

If things are feeling stagnant and not changing, ask yourself what have I been procrastinating on?

If you know you’re ready for something new: new love, new clients, or a new lifestyle….you need to let go of the old one!

What is the surest way to create change i your life? Make space for it. 

You have to clear out the old in order to create space for the new. Energetically it is that simple!

So I challenge you this week (or even better this month) to clear out 5 things every day from your life that it’s time to let go of.

Whether it’s clothes, things around the house, old emails or photos clogging up your phone…it’s time for it to go!

Notice how it feels. Notice what shifts. Notice what new energy starts to flow ✨

Let me know in the comments - what are you letting go of?

Some days just don’t feel as good as others.

Some days taking care of my energy is a full time job. 

Some days we’re moving through something, or something needs to move through us. 

Some days just feel different, like there’s something in the air that leaves us feeling heavy and stuck, finding it hard to focus, or riding waves of emotions.

Today was one of those for me.

They used to leave me confused, full of guilt, or blaming myself for not being able to “just feel good”. Sometimes I used to wonder if there was something wrong with me when I felt like I had days of just not being as productive as I’d wanted or showing up in the ways I expected myself to.

Now, Ive learnt to just ride the waves. To realise it’s all just part of the journey. It’s all just energy moving through us and around us.

Now I know on days like these that I have the tools to support me, and I feel so grateful to be able to hold myself in all my humanness. 

Especially as healers or empaths (or just humans, because we all do feel it no matter how aware we are of it) we are always feeling energy. We pick up things that aren’t ours, maybe our energy changes with the moon or with the energy of others around us.

Shifting and clearing my energy is something I do every day, or moment to moment as I need it. And learning how to take care of yours is a powerful way to help you feel better, move through stuckness and show up in the way you really want to.

Those moments won’t come.

It’s about asking yourself, what am I choosing? What am I prioritising? Am I ready to choose myself and my dreams?

When I get stuck in the fear or scarcity or doubt, or old money mindsets come back up to haunt me in moments when I’m investing in my dreams…these are some of my favourite ways to reframe those beliefs and help me shift back into the energy of abundance ✨

✨Money is energy. When you invest in yourself, you’re really just directing energy towards your dreams.

✨ Energy needs to flow. Keep it moving and more will flow in.

✨How will you feel if you don’t do it and stay stuck where you are instead?

✨When you invest in something that’s aligned with your dreams, you also support whoever is giving you their service or expertise. It’s not losing money, it’s sharing abundance!

Which one resonates with you the most? Share it to your story and spread the abundance!

This week I’ve been hearing the same thing again and again in sessions with my clients, and reading messages from you all in my inbox, it seems like everyone is feeling the same way….

Stuck. Overwhelmed. All over the place. Confused. Uncertain. Lost. Questioning things.

…sound familiar?

And what I’ve been learning as I move through some of these sticky emotions with my clients (and for myself - I’ve been feeling it too!) is that underneath there’s really just one thing:

Fear.

Fear shows up in the funniest of disguises. Sometimes we don’t even realise that it’s fear that’s really underneath what we’re feeling.

Oftentimes feeling stuck is our fight/flight/freeze response getting triggered. And underneath that is a fear that’s stopping us from moving forward.

These are normally very old, root fears like - not feeling safe, fear of abandonment or rejection, or not feeling good enough. 

The antidote to that fear? Trust.

Nurturing the part of you that is underneath the stuckness that needs to feel safe, loved, and accepted.

Taking yourself out of the fight/flight response by reminding yourself of all the reasons that you’re actually safe and everything is ok.

Imagine if you could operate from a frequency based in trust instead of one based in fear?

How would that feel in your body? How would that show up in your life?

For a long time in my life I felt like I couldn’t really be myself.

I felt like the “weird” one. I was afraid to be “too much” in case people didn’t like me. I always felt different, on the outside, seeing things differently from everyone else.

So I changed myself to fit in. I tried to fit into a perfect mold of how I “should” be. I made myself smaller, I dimmed my light. I followed the path that I was “supposed” to take, to be a good girl, to be “successful”. 

I made myself less and less until I forgot that I was more than that. 

I forgot that I wasn’t being fully me, and just learned to live with an endless ache in my soul telling me that something was missing.

For the longest time, I felt like I was waiting for my real life to start.

This week I had an amazing moment of healing, in a guided visualisation where I connected with my inner teenager.

That old version of me who was trying her hardest to be like everyone else, and losing herself in the process.

And I told her: “you don’t have to fit in. Just be yourself.”

I saw her, seeing me, as I am now. And I saw the deep knowing of recognition on her face.

That even though I wasn’t who she imagined, or believed she could have the power to become, something deep inside of her wasn’t surprised. 

Because she recognised in me the embodiment of everything that she truly was inside. All the dreams she longed for but didn’t even imagine could come true.

And I imagined if I had met myself now, back then. What a weight would have been lifted in realising that I didn’t need to do it the same way as anyone else.

That I was going to end up exactly where I was meant to be. As exactly who I truly was.

So just remember, however stuck you might feel right now or however far you feel like you still have to go…

There is a past version of you who would be SO proud to see everything you’ve become. ✨✨✨

I get asked this questions a lot by my clients, other healers and sound healing students…✨

How do you protect your energy?

As a healer or an empath, you probably a very sensitive to energy.

Maybe you notice that you feel drained after being in certain environments or around certain people. Maybe you find yourself taking on other people’s energy and losing sight of your own.

And the more you awaken your healing gifts, the more sensitive you can become.

If you’re opening yourself up more with energy healing or sound healing, it’s a beautiful path but can also mean that you start to be even more aware of the other energy around you! 

So protecting your energy is SO important for your own well-being. And for the energy you’re able to bring into your work!

This is my favourite technique to protect my energy. I use it in sessions, when I need to take care of myself, or even if I’m just heading into a busy part of town, or into an intense conversation with someone else to make sure I can stay in my own vibe instead of getting swept away in other people’s energy! ✨

✨ Sit in meditation and tune into how it feels to be in your own energy

✨ As you inhale, imagine a bright white light shining and growing in your heart space. 

✨ As you exhale, imagine this light expanding and shining out of you to surround you with a bubble of energy

✨ Imagine this bubble like a forcefield protecting you and keeping you in your own energy. You can see out and interact, but other energy can’t get in.

✨ Any time you feel yourself getting lost or affected by other energy, take a deep breath and visualise your energy bubble surrounding you. 

…try it out and let me know how it feels in the comments! 🙏🏼✨

On the morning before I flew to Italy, I was in total panic.

There was even a moment when I didn’t even know if I would go.

….and do you know why?

Because I was leaving my comfort zone.

I got soooo comfortable staying at my parents house this summer. I was in my zone, I had my work routine down, things were flowing so perfectly (not to mention, I could just relax in my childhood room and have all my meals made for me 😂). My nervous system felt so good.

I was so comfortable, that suddenly leaving felt impossible.

My mind started to tell me all kinds of stories about why I shouldn’t go - how it would be bad for my business, how I wouldn’t have fun, how I wouldn’t get my work done and everything would fall apart.

It was so interesting to witness. Because this was happening FOR ME, someone who is used to traveling all the time, working from anywhere, and always making brave moves.

I knew that I can trust my business to work wherever I am.

I knew that I wanted to go on this beautiful trip to see my love and his my family and have more adventures in Italy.

I have proof that my business actually thrives MORE the more I relax and enjoy my life.

…and yet, still my comfort zone wanted me to stay.

It made me realise just how hard it can be to take steps that change things, even when you know it’s what you want.

Even when you know it’s good for you.

Even when you know it’s taking you towards the life you want.

We still all get scared. Our mind will still always make up stories about why we shouldn’t take the leap.

I was sitting on the beach in the morning doing my morning practice and watching the giant pre-storm waves coming in.

I could feel the energy of the incoming storm.

The intensity of what was building out in the ocean.
The little frisson of fear and anticipation inside me.

And I realised that we’re always feeling the energy of what is happening in nature, what is happening around us.

And that there is always a lesson or an invitation in what life brings to us.

Every storm, whether it’s a real-life hurricane, a curveball life throws at you or an emotional storm to work your way through, is an invitation to learn something.

To go within and find your own inner stillness, to strengthen your own inner resilience and the knowing that you can weather any storm life brings.

We can’t control the fact that there will always be storms for us to pass through in life, any more than we can try to control the weather.

Instead of resisting, ask, how can I use this as an invitation to grow.m? To embrace my own wildness and release what I need to release. Or to go within and build my own shelter inside myself.

I realised that this is what I’ve done this year, in my life and in my business.

I’ve built strong foundations, the resilience and self-trust to know that I can deal with anything that comes.

I know that my work (and me!) can support me no matter what.

No matter where I am, no matter what might happen. Even if life happens and things change, I know that I can weather any storm. I’ve proven it time and time again.

I thought back to the girl I was 5 years ago, living in London and feeling so lost.

Stuck in toxic relationships and toxic habits.

Feeling totally out of connection with myself and my purpose.

My soul longed for something more, but I couldn’t see beyond what I thought I was “supposed to do.”

I started following the whispers of my soul, without knowing where they would lead.

I travelled to Bali. I became a yoga teacher. I realised just how much I needed to heal. I started to find myself again.

Keep listening.
